nodes.text: Sue Murphy is a stand-up comedian who has worked on such shows as Short Attention Span Theater, The Jeff Foxworthy Show, Comedy Central Presents and Wanda Does It. In 1986, she provided the voice of Latara in the second season of Ewoks, taking over for Taborah Johnson. Murphy has also been a producer and writer on The Ellen DeGeneres Show, The Class and Wanda at Large and appeared in the movie Nine Months. In 2001 she was honored with a nomination for the American Comedy Award for Best Female Stand-Up.
